  "text": "Here the vector Φ ∈ R d defines the direction of the projection, and λ is a scalar chosen such that the new approximationX t,x belongs to the invariant submanifold M x properly. The general idea of the procedures is shown in Fig.  1 . In fact the projection direction Φ is not unique here, and the standard orthogonal projection chooses ∇I(X t,x ) as Φ(x,X t,x ) [CITATION_1] Chap. IV] . In order to reduce computational cost we just use ∇I( X t,x ) or ∇I(x) to replace ∇I(X t,x ). So we combine the relationship and getX t,x above by solving a non-linear equation with respect to λ. In fact, we find that λ approaches 0 at each step, so we just set λ 0 = 0 in Newton iteration to solve it.",
